    "intro": "Interpretation asks what Psalm 86 *means* — moving from what the text says to what the psalmist intended in his historical and canonical context. The movements below trace the psalm's argument through its three cycles. Each pericope is held within the canonical thread running from Exodus 34:6 through the Psalter and forward into the New Testament's understanding of prayer and divine character. Where the original Hebrew sharpens an English translation, a brief note follows the exposition.",
